record_data.record_title: Revenue Requirement for Reactive Supply and Voltage Control
record_data.record_plain_text:
Title Page pursuant to 18 C.F.R. ? 35.10(a)
Filing Entity Municipal Energy Agency of Mississippi Recipient of Service Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. Description of Service Provision of Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service from MEAM's Ownership Interest in the Plum Point Energy Station
THE MUNICIPAL ENERGY AGENCY OF MISSISSIPPI SPECIFICATION OF COST-BASED REVENUE REQUIREMENT FOR THE PROVISION OF REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE (PLUM POINT ENERGY STATION) The Municipal Energy Agency of Mississippi ("MEAM") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Service") from its 6.0% ownership interest in the Plum Point Energy Station, an electric generation facility located near Osceola, Arkansas ("Facility") that is interconnected to the transmission system operated by the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO"). This Specification sets forth MEAM's cost-based annual and monthly revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Service from MEAM's ownership share of the Facility pursuant to Schedule 2 of the MISO Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserve Markets Tariff. 1. Annual Revenue Requirement. MEAM's annual revenue requirement for providing Reactive Service from Plum Point consists of the Fixed Capability Component calculated in accordance with FERC-approved methods. The annual revenue requirement for the Fixed Capability Component is $60,842.00 per year. 2. Monthly Revenue Requirement: MEAM's monthly revenue requirement for providing Reactive Service from Plum Point is equal to the annual revenue requirement divided by 12, or $5,070.17 per month. 3. Effective Date: This Rate Schedule shall be effective on and after May 1, 2015, or such other date as is directed by the FERC, and shall remain in effect until modified or canceled pursuant to filings made with FERC.
